<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1438,151,1077]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,151,176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Description.</emphasis>
Colony encrusting, uni- to multilaminar. Zooids hexagonal, becoming polygonal with growth, longer than wide, delimited by distinct grooves. Frontal shield heavily calcified, uniformly punctured by 20–50 pseudopores, minutely granular. Primary orifice large relative to frontal shield, centered, somewhat hoof-shaped, mostly as long as wide, sunken, with arch-shaped anter and concave poster, separated by 2 proximolateral downcurved condyles. Secondary orifice non-tubercular, slightly raised, surrounded by pseudopores. Frontal avicularia small, elliptical, often single (rarely 2 per zooid), placed at zooidal margins. Ooecium subglobose, minutely granular, inclined toward zooid surface; ectooecium with longitudinal band of 33–48 irregular pseudopores.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1438,151,1077]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,404,429]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[332,540,404,429]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="porosa">
<emphasis box="[332,540,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Cigclisula porosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Canu, F. &amp; Bassler, R. S." box="[787,1088,404,429]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 92" refId="ref30220" refString="Canu, F. &amp; Bassler, R. S. (1930 a) The Bryozoan Fauna of the Galapagos Islands. Proceedings of United States National Museum, Smithsonian Institution, Washington, 76 (2810), 1 - 92." type="journal article" year="1930">Canu &amp; Bassler (1930a)</bibRefCitation>
in the same publication as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Canu &amp; Bassler, 1930)" baseAuthorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[151,759,439,464]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="hexagonalis">
<emphasis box="[151,454,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Trematooecia hexagonalis</emphasis>
(Canu &amp; Bassler, 1930)
</taxonomicName>
. While the ectooecium of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[1098,1215,440,464]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="porosa">
<emphasis box="[1098,1215,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">C. porosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described as pseudoporous, 
<bibRefCitation author="Canu, F. &amp; Bassler, R. S." box="[325,610,476,501]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 92" refId="ref30220" refString="Canu, F. &amp; Bassler, R. S. (1930 a) The Bryozoan Fauna of the Galapagos Islands. Proceedings of United States National Museum, Smithsonian Institution, Washington, 76 (2810), 1 - 92." type="journal article" year="1930">Canu &amp; Bassler (1930a)</bibRefCitation>
did not recognize ooecia in the 
<typeStatus box="[999,1097,476,501]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[1144,1311,476,501]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="hexagonalis">
<emphasis box="[1144,1311,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">T. hexagonalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but some authors (
<bibRefCitation author="Osburn, R. C." box="[247,397,511,536]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="271 - 611" refId="ref31697" refString="Osburn, R. C. (1952) Bryozoa of the Pacific coast of America, part 2, Cheilostomata - Ascophora. Report of the Allan Hancock Pacific Expeditions, 14, 271 - 611." type="journal article" year="1952">Osburn 1952</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Soule, J. D." box="[408,537,511,536]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 66" refId="ref32035" refString="Soule, J. D. (1961) Results of the Puritan-American Museum of Natural History expedition to western Mexico. 13. Ascophoran Cheilostomata (Bryozoa) of the Gulf of California. American Museum Novitates, 2053, 1 - 66." type="journal article" year="1961">Soule 1961</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Soule, D. F. &amp; Soule, J. D." box="[549,775,511,536]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 56" refId="ref32080" refString="Soule, D. F. &amp; Soule, J. D. (1964) The Ectoprocta (Bryozoa) of Scammon's Lagoon, Baja California, Mexico. American Museum Novitates, 2199, 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1964">Soule &amp; Soule 1964</bibRefCitation>
) described the ectooecium of this species as pseudoporous, designating these specimens as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[510,674,548,573]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="hexagonalis">
<emphasis box="[510,674,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">T. hexagonalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[914,1012,548,573]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[1052,1215,548,573]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="hexagonalis">
<emphasis box="[1052,1215,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">T. hexagonalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, revealed that the ectooecium has single median membranous area (see remarks under 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[1034,1198,583,608]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="hexagonalis">
<emphasis box="[1034,1198,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">T. hexagonalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) contrasting with an irregularly pseudoporous ectooecium, which is distinct in 
<emphasis box="[811,929,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[811,925,620,644]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="porosa">C. porosa</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Besides the ectooecium and tubercles, other differences between these two species include the diameter of frontal pseudopores, larger in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[1316,1436,656,680]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="porosa">
<emphasis box="[1316,1436,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">C. porosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity box="[158,353,692,717]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3499999999999996" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.0235" valueMax="0.032" valueMin="0.015">
<geoCoordinate box="[158,221,692,717]" degrees="0.015" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" precision="55" value="0.015">0.015</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[221,300,692,717]" degrees="0.032" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" precision="55" value="-0.032">–0.032</geoCoordinate>
mm
</quantity>
) than in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[452,615,692,717]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="hexagonalis">
<emphasis box="[452,615,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">T. hexagonalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity box="[631,828,692,717]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.7999999999999998" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.013999999999999999" valueMax="0.018" valueMin="0.01">
