<bibRefCitation author="Osburn, R. C." box="[974,1122,764,789]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="271 - 611" refId="ref31697" refString="Osburn, R. C. (1952) Bryozoa of the Pacific coast of America, part 2, Cheilostomata - Ascophora. Report of the Allan Hancock Pacific Expeditions, 14, 271 - 611." type="journal article" year="1952">Osburn 1952</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Soule, J. D." box="[1133,1262,764,789]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 66" refId="ref32035" refString="Soule, J. D. (1961) Results of the Puritan-American Museum of Natural History expedition to western Mexico. 13. Ascophoran Cheilostomata (Bryozoa) of the Gulf of California. American Museum Novitates, 2053, 1 - 66." type="journal article" year="1961">Soule 1961</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Soule, D. F. &amp; Soule, J. D." pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 56" refId="ref32080" refString="Soule, D. F. &amp; Soule, J. D. (1964) The Ectoprocta (Bryozoa) of Scammon's Lagoon, Baja California, Mexico. American Museum Novitates, 2199, 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1964">Soule &amp; Soule 1964</bibRefCitation>
) are here reassigned to 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[473,681,799,824]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="osburni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[473,681,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Cigclisula osburni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[688,748,800,823]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(see below).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1438,151,1077]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[199,399,836,861]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="porosa">
<emphasis box="[199,399,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Cigclisula porosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by encrusting colonies with the zooidal frontal shield uniformly punctured by 20–50 pseudopores, primary orifice almost rounded with distolateral condyles, secondary orifice nontubercular, elliptical frontal avicularia and ectooecium with 33–48 irregular pseudopores. This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Livingstone" authorityYear="1926" box="[151,282,943,968]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Bryocryptellidae" genus="Porella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="areolata">
<emphasis box="[151,282,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">C. areolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having encrusting colonies, a uniformly punctured frontal shield and non-tubercular secondary orifice, but differs in the the hoof-shaped primary orifice (transversely D-shaped in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Livingstone" authorityYear="1926" box="[1087,1214,980,1005]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Bryocryptellidae" genus="Porella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="areolata">
<emphasis box="[1087,1214,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">C. areolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and in the absence of suboral and interzooidal avicularia (present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Livingstone" authorityYear="1926" box="[702,829,1015,1040]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Bryocryptellidae" genus="Porella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="areolata">
<emphasis box="[702,829,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">C. areolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
